## Run the app from within a Google Cloud Compute Engine Virtual Machine

# If you do not yet have a Virtual Machine instance in Google Cloud Compute Engine (https://console.cloud.google.com/compute/instances), go to the next section to create an instance before proceeding.

1.  Start your Patent Application VM instance in Google Cloud Compute Engine, then click the SSH button to open a new terminal window for the VM.

2.  Activate your Patent Application environment by entering the following into the command line:

    source ~/patent_app_venv/bin/activate

3.  Navigate to the directory containing the Patent Comparison application files:

    cd project-mountainstar/RAG\ Model\ Package/

4.  Activate the application and wait for the hyperlink to appear:

    ./app_start.sh

5.  Once the link appears, copy it to your browser window.


## Create and run a Virtual Machine (VM) in Google Cloud Compute Engine

Run the below commands to create a virtual machine that can run the app.
You only need to run this section once per virtual machine.

1. Go to Google Cloud Compute Engine Instances (https://console.cloud.google.com/compute/instances)

2. Click the blue "Create instance" button at the top of the page. 
    
    a. Follow the prompts to create an instance.
    b. Minimum system requirements:
        - 16 vCPUs
        - 104 GB RAM
        - Recommend Linux Deep Learning VM with CUDA + Pytorch, M131, Ubuntu 24.04, CUDA 12.8, Pytorch 2.7, Python 3.12 or higher
    c. Be sure to set which APIs the VM can access, any security requirements, and login requirements.

3. Once the VM is created, ensure it is running by looking for the green check mark next to the instance name.

    a. If the instance is not running, click the check box next to the instance name and click the Start button at the top of the page.

4. Once the VM is running, click the "SSH" button to the right of the instance name. This will open a terminal window for the VM in a new window.

5. Copy and paste the following commands into the terminal window one at a time and hit return:

    a.  sudo apt-get update   # update the system

    b.  Depending on your selected Linux distribution, you may need to create and activate a virtual environment:
    
        i.  python3 -m venv ~/patent_app_venv   # create a virtual environment for the app

        ii.  source ~/patent_app_venv/bin/activate   # run the virtual environment
    
    d.  pip install --upgrade pip   # make sure you have the latest version of pip

    e.  pip install pandas PyArrow numpy faiss-cpu torch scikit-learn tqdm sentence-transformers gcsfs fsspec google-cloud-storage google-cloud-bigquery Pillow requests lxml networkx streamlit-autorefresh papermill pyvis matplotlib wordcloud beautifulsoup4
        -- Depending on your selected Linux distribution, you may need to use sudo pip install
        # install all of the dependencies
    
    f.  curl -L https://pkg.cloudflare.com/cloudflare-main.gpg | sudo tee /usr/share/keyrings/cloudflare-archive-keyring.gpg >/dev/null
        echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/cloudflare-archive-keyring.gpg] https://pkg.cloudflare.com/cloudflared any main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/cloudflared.list
        sudo apt-get update
        sudo apt-get install cloudflared
        # install cloudflared
    
    c.  pip install ipykernel   # install ipykernel

        i. If you are using a virtual environment, also run this step:
            python -m ipykernel install --user --name=embedding_loader_venv --display-name "Python (patent_app_venv)"   # register the kernel with Jupyter

6. Upload all files and directories from the RAG Model Package directory. Recommended method:
    
    git clone https://github.com/HollyIrvine/project-mountainstar.git
    
        - input login name and access token when prompted
        - access token can be created at https://github.com/settings/tokens
    
7.  Navigate to the folder containing the RAG model files:
    
    cd project-mountainstar/RAG\ Model\ Package/

8.  Ensure you are in the patent_app_venv (command line should start with (patent_app_venv) followed by your login name), then make the app_start.py file executable by running the following commands, one at a time:

    chmod +x app_start.sh
    sed -i 's/\r$//' app_start.sh

9.  You can now run ./app_start.sh from within the RAG Model Package directory.


